走向佢嘅時候,佢就同佢嘅門徒講

224
00:11:41,340 --> 00:11:46,340
佢話,舉目向田觀看,莊稼熟了

225
00:11:46,340 --> 00:11:50,340
They had heard the woman's testimony

226
00:11:50,340 --> 00:11:52,340
佢哋聽到呢個女人嘅見證

227
00:11:52,340 --> 00:11:55,340
And now they came out to experience the Messiah

228
00:11:55,340 --> 00:11:59,340
而家佢出嚟,佢親身咁經歷彌賽亞

229
00:11:59,340 --> 00:12:02,340
Pain can be productive

230
00:12:02,340 --> 00:12:04,340
痛苦可能有生產力

231
00:12:04,340 --> 00:12:06,340
There is purpose in pain

232
00:12:06,340 --> 00:12:08,340
我哋嘅痛苦係有目的嘅

233
00:12:08,340 --> 00:12:11,340
Suffering can accomplish something

234
00:12:11,340 --> 00:12:13,340
苦難可以成就一啲嘅事

235
00:12:13,340 --> 00:12:16,340
From misery to God's mission

236
00:12:16,340 --> 00:12:18,340
By faith

237
00:12:18,340 --> 00:12:24,340
從苦難,憑著信心去到達咗神嘅使命

238
00:12:24,340 --> 00:12:26,340
So this morning we will see in the Old Testament

239
00:12:26,340 --> 00:12:30,340
Another woman named Naomi

240
00:12:30,340 --> 00:12:35,340
今日我哋喺舊約聖經中睇到嘅一個女人叫蘭娥米

241
00:12:35,340 --> 00:12:37,340
She also experienced misery

242
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:41,340
But she traveled from her tragedy by way of trust

243
00:12:41,340 --> 00:12:44,340
And found God's grace and triumph

244
00:12:44,340 --> 00:12:46,340
呢個女人佢亦都經歷咗痛苦

245
00:12:46,340 --> 00:12:49,340
但透過佢嘅信心同埋佢嘅尋求

246
00:12:49,340 --> 00:12:52,340
佢喺上帝度搵到得勝

247
00:12:52,340 --> 00:12:56,340
Let's look at our passage

248
00:12:56,340 --> 00:12:59,340
Ruth chapter 1 verses 11 through 18

249
00:12:59,340 --> 00:13:02,340
我哋睇下路德記第一章十一至十八節

250
00:13:02,340 --> 00:13:05,340
But Naomi said to her daughter-in-law

251
00:13:05,340 --> 00:13:07,340
"Return home, my daughters

252
00:13:07,340 --> 00:13:09,340
Why would you come with me?

253
00:13:09,340 --> 00:13:11,340
Am I going to have any more sons?

254
00:13:11,340 --> 00:13:13,340
Who could become your husbands?"

255
00:13:13,340 --> 00:13:16,340
蘭娥米說,我的女兒會去爸

256
00:13:16,340 --> 00:13:18,340
為何要跟從我呢?

257
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:21,340
我還能生兒子作你們的丈夫嗎?

258
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:27,340
"Return home, I am too old to have another husband

259
00:13:27,340 --> 00:13:30,340
Even if I thought there was still hope for me

260
00:13:30,340 --> 00:13:32,340
Even if I had a husband tonight

261
00:13:32,340 --> 00:13:35,340
And then gave birth to sons"

262
00:13:35,340 --> 00:13:37,340
我的兒女呀,會去爸

263
00:13:37,340 --> 00:13:39,340
我的年紀老了,不能再有丈夫

264
00:13:39,340 --> 00:13:41,340
就算我還有希望

265
00:13:41,340 --> 00:13:43,340
今夜有丈夫,而且也生了兒子

266
00:13:43,340 --> 00:13:46,340
"Would you wait until they grew up?

267
00:13:46,340 --> 00:13:48,340
Would you remain unmarried for them?

268
00:13:48,340 --> 00:13:52,340
Know, my daughters, it is more bitter for me than for you

269
00:13:52,340 --> 00:13:55,340
Because the Lord's hand has turned against me"

270
00:13:55,340 --> 00:13:58,340
你們豈能等著他們長大呢?

271
00:13:58,340 --> 00:14:00,340
你們能守住自己不嫁人嗎?

272
00:14:00,340 --> 00:14:02,340
我的女兒呀,不要這樣

273
00:14:02,340 --> 00:14:04,340
我比你們更苦

274
00:14:04,340 --> 00:14:07,340
因為耶和華的新手擊打我

275
00:14:07,340 --> 00:14:11,340
"They wept aloud again

276
00:14:11,340 --> 00:14:14,340
And Orpah kissed her mother-in-law goodbye

277
00:14:14,340 --> 00:14:17,340
But Ruth clung to her"

278
00:14:17,340 --> 00:14:21,340
在十四節說到兩個媳婦又放聲大哭

279
00:14:21,340 --> 00:14:23,340
Orpah與婆婆吻別

280
00:14:23,340 --> 00:14:27,340
但是魯德卻緊跟著蘭娥米

281
00:14:27,340 --> 00:14:31,340
"Look," said Naomi

282
00:14:31,340 --> 00:14:34,340
"Your sister-in-law is going back to her people

283
00:14:34,340 --> 00:14:37,340
And to her gods, go back with her

284
00:14:37,340 --> 00:14:40,340
But Ruth replied, 'Don't urge me to leave you

285
00:14:40,340 --> 00:14:42,340
Or to turn back from you

286
00:14:42,340 --> 00:14:44,340
Where you go, I will go

287
00:14:44,340 --> 00:14:46,340
Where you stay, I will stay

288
00:14:46,340 --> 00:14:48,340
Your people will be my people

289
00:14:48,340 --> 00:14:51,340
And your god, my god"

290
00:14:51,340 --> 00:14:52,340
蘭娥米說

291
00:14:52,340 --> 00:14:56,340
"漢啊,你嫂嫂已經回到她的百姓和她的神明那裏去了

292
00:14:56,340 --> 00:14:59,340
你也跟你的嫂嫂回去吧

293
00:14:59,340 --> 00:15:01,340
魯德說,不要勸我離開你

294
00:15:01,340 --> 00:15:03,340
轉去不跟隨你

295
00:15:03,340 --> 00:15:05,340
你往哪裏去,我也往哪裏去

296
00:15:05,340 --> 00:15:07,340
你在哪裏住,我也在哪裏住

297
00:15:07,340 --> 00:15:09,340
你的百姓就是我的百姓

298
00:15:09,340 --> 00:15:11,340
你的神就是我的神"

299
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:14,340
"And where you die, I will die

300
00:15:14,340 --> 00:15:16,340
And there I will be buried

301
00:15:16,340 --> 00:15:19,340
May the Lord deal with me, be it ever so severely

302
00:15:19,340 --> 00:15:22,340
If even death separates you and me"

303
00:15:22,340 --> 00:15:26,340
And when Naomi realized that Ruth was determined

304
00:15:26,340 --> 00:15:29,340
To go with her, she stopped urging her

305
00:15:29,340 --> 00:15:32,340
"你死在哪裏,我也死在哪裏,葬在哪裏

306
00:15:32,340 --> 00:15:34,340
只有死能使你與我分離

307
00:15:34,340 --> 00:15:37,340
不言怨言和話,重重懲罰我

308
00:15:37,340 --> 00:15:40,340
蘭娥米見,魯德決意要跟自己去

309
00:15:40,340 --> 00:15:43,340
就不再對她說什麼了"

310
00:15:43,340 --> 00:15:48,340
Wow, can you feel this passage this morning?

311
00:15:48,340 --> 00:15:51,340
你有沒有感受到今天這段經文?

312
00:15:51,340 --> 00:15:53,340
Perhaps you know moving and making new friends

313
00:15:53,340 --> 00:15:56,340
and adjusting to a new area

314
00:15:56,340 --> 00:15:59,340
are challenging situations

315
00:15:59,340 --> 00:16:01,340
或者你會知道,搬到一個新地方

316
00:16:01,340 --> 00:16:03,340
去認識新的朋友,去適應這個環境

317
00:16:03,340 --> 00:16:05,340
是可以有挑戰性的

318
00:16:05,340 --> 00:16:08,340
The story of Ruth and Naomi's move

319
00:16:08,340 --> 00:16:13,340
is from Moab, a Gentile city

320
00:16:13,340 --> 00:16:17,340
back to Bethlehem in Israel or in Judah

321
00:16:17,340 --> 00:16:21,340
and also a move that would have been full of misery

322
00:16:21,340 --> 00:16:25,340
蘭娥米從摩訶這個異教的國家

323
00:16:25,340 --> 00:16:27,340
回到白里行的故事

324
00:16:27,340 --> 00:16:29,340
也是充滿著痛苦的

325
00:16:29,340 --> 00:16:33,340
Maybe you remember Ruth's Jewish mother-in-law Naomi

326
00:16:33,340 --> 00:16:37,340
and father-in-law Elimelech had two sons

327
00:16:37,340 --> 00:16:40,340
Milan and Kilian

328
00:16:40,340 --> 00:16:42,340
and they had moved to Moab

329
00:16:42,340 --> 00:16:45,340
during a great famine in Canaan

330
00:16:45,340 --> 00:16:48,340
或者你會記得,路德這個猶太的奶奶

331
00:16:48,340 --> 00:16:51,340
蘭娥米和她的老爺伊利米勒

332
00:16:51,340 --> 00:16:54,340
她有兩個兒子叫做馬倫和基蓮

333
00:16:54,340 --> 00:16:56,340
是從加南,在饑荒的時候

334
00:16:56,340 --> 00:16:58,340
搬到去摸鴨的

335
00:16:58,340 --> 00:17:02,340
While living in Moab, the two Jewish sons

336
00:17:02,340 --> 00:17:07,340
of Naomi married a Gentile

337
00:17:07,340 --> 00:17:09,340
Gentile women, Orpah and Ruth

338
00:17:09,340 --> 00:17:11,340
住在摩訶的期間

339
00:17:11,340 --> 00:17:14,340
蘭娥米的兩個猶太兒子

340
00:17:14,340 --> 00:17:17,340
娶了摩訶艾邦的女子為妻

341
00:17:17,340 --> 00:17:19,340
娶了俄爾巴和路德為妻

342
00:17:19,340 --> 00:17:21,340
Now we're not told the circumstances

343
00:17:21,340 --> 00:17:24,340
but Naomi's husband died

344
00:17:24,340 --> 00:17:27,340
and her two sons also died

345
00:17:27,340 --> 00:17:32,340
Leaving Naomi, Orpah and Ruth as widows

346
00:17:32,340 --> 00:17:36,340
and they would have been in a totally desperate

347
00:17:36,340 --> 00:17:39,340
and a total miserable situation

348
00:17:39,340 --> 00:17:41,340
我們不知道當時的情況

349
00:17:41,340 --> 00:17:43,340
蘭娥米的丈夫過世

350
00:17:43,340 --> 00:17:45,340
然後兩個兒子也去世

351
00:17:45,340 --> 00:17:49,340
留下了蘭娥米、俄爾巴和路德成為寡婦

352
00:17:49,340 --> 00:17:51,340
我們可以想像一下

353
00:17:51,340 --> 00:17:53,340
他們當時是多麼的痛苦

354
00:17:53,340 --> 00:17:54,340
They would have been alone

355
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:56,340
他們當時是很孤單的

356
00:17:56,340 --> 00:17:59,340
They would have been without their husbands

357
00:17:59,340 --> 00:18:01,340
因為他們沒有了他們的丈夫

358
00:18:01,340 --> 00:18:02,340
Without their sons

359
00:18:02,340 --> 00:18:03,340
沒有了他們的兒子

360
00:18:03,340 --> 00:18:05,340
and basically without a future

361
00:18:05,340 --> 00:18:06,340
in that culture

362
00:18:06,340 --> 00:18:09,340
其實在那種習俗之中是沒有將來的

363
00:18:09,340 --> 00:18:11,340
But the story goes on to say that

364
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:14,340
Naomi learned that there was no longer a famine

365
00:18:14,340 --> 00:18:16,340
in her homeland of Judah

366
00:18:16,340 --> 00:18:19,340
and so she decided to move back to her homeland

367
00:18:19,340 --> 00:18:21,340
故事繼續就是蘭娥米得知

368
00:18:21,340 --> 00:18:24,340
她的祖國猶大不再有饑荒

369
00:18:24,340 --> 00:18:26,340
所以決定她要搬回她的家鄉

370
00:18:26,340 --> 00:18:29,340
So Naomi must have been preparing to go back

371
00:18:29,340 --> 00:18:30,340
packing her things

372
00:18:30,340 --> 00:18:32,340
and she turned and she saw

373
00:18:32,340 --> 00:18:35,340
Orpah and Ruth following after her

374
00:18:35,340 --> 00:18:38,340
蘭娥米一定在收拾行李

375
00:18:38,340 --> 00:18:40,340
她轉身看到兩個媳婦

376
00:18:40,340 --> 00:18:42,340
俄爾巴和路德在跟隨她

377
00:18:42,340 --> 00:18:44,340
And then in verse 8 we see

378
00:18:44,340 --> 00:18:45,340
she says go back

379
00:18:45,340 --> 00:18:48,340
and each of you to your mother's home

380
00:18:48,340 --> 00:18:51,340
May the Lord show you kindness

381
00:18:51,340 --> 00:18:53,340
as you have shown to your dead husbands

382
00:18:53,340 --> 00:18:55,340
And to me, may the Lord grant

383
00:18:55,340 --> 00:18:57,340
that each of you will find rest

384
00:18:57,340 --> 00:19:00,340
in the home of another husband

385
00:19:00,340 --> 00:19:02,340
在第八節,蘭娥米就跟她的媳婦說

386
00:19:02,340 --> 00:19:04,340
你們各自回娘家去吧

387
00:19:04,340 --> 00:19:06,340
願耶和華待你們

388
00:19:06,340 --> 00:19:08,340
將你們待已故的人和我一樣

389
00:19:08,340 --> 00:19:12,340
願耶和華使你各在自己新的丈夫家中得歸宿

390
00:19:12,340 --> 00:19:15,340
You can't really fault Naomi, can you?

391
00:19:15,340 --> 00:19:17,340
I mean, she's wanting to go back home

392
00:19:17,340 --> 00:19:19,340
where she has family members

393
00:19:19,340 --> 00:19:21,340
and where she's familiar

394
00:19:21,340 --> 00:19:23,340
所以怪責蘭娥米

395
00:19:23,340 --> 00:19:25,340
想回她的家鄉祖國

396
00:19:25,340 --> 00:19:28,340
因為她想離開她的親戚朋友近一點

397
00:19:28,340 --> 00:19:31,340
Maybe some of you have experienced

398
00:19:31,340 --> 00:19:34,340
the loss of a spouse

399
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:36,340
或者你們中間有些人

400
00:19:36,340 --> 00:19:39,340
可能已經經歷過失去了配偶

401
00:19:39,340 --> 00:19:41,340
It's not easy living alone

402
00:19:41,340 --> 00:19:44,340
一個人生活是不簡單的

403
00:19:44,340 --> 00:19:47,340
But she encouraged her daughter-in-laws

404
00:19:47,340 --> 00:19:50,340
to stay with her own people

405
00:19:50,340 --> 00:19:53,340
and to find a husband to provide for their needs

406
00:19:53,340 --> 00:19:55,340
但是她鼓勵自己兩個媳婦

407
00:19:55,340 --> 00:19:57,340
回到自己的民族那裡

408
00:19:57,340 --> 00:20:00,340
去找到一個新的丈夫來滿足他們的需求

409
00:20:00,340 --> 00:20:02,340
And then we see in verse 14 and 15

410
00:20:02,340 --> 00:20:05,340
at this they wept aloud

411
00:20:05,340 --> 00:20:09,340
and Orpah kissed her mother-in-law goodbye

412
00:20:09,340 --> 00:20:12,340
But Ruth clung to her

413
00:20:12,340 --> 00:20:14,340
Look, said Naomi

414
00:20:14,340 --> 00:20:18,340
Your sister-in-law, she's going back to her people

415
00:20:18,340 --> 00:20:21,340
to her gods, go back with her

416
00:20:21,340 --> 00:20:23,340
在第十四、第十五節

417
00:20:23,340 --> 00:20:25,340
娥米吻別了兩個媳婦

418
00:20:25,340 --> 00:20:27,340
然後開始回家的旅程

419
00:20:27,340 --> 00:20:29,340
經過一場勸告

420
00:20:29,340 --> 00:20:31,340
娥爾巴已經轉身回去了

421
00:20:31,340 --> 00:20:36,340
但是路德就抓住他的婆婆

422
00:20:36,340 --> 00:20:38,340
他緊緊抓住娥米

423
00:20:38,340 --> 00:20:39,340
沒有轉身

424
00:20:39,340 --> 00:20:40,340
娥米就跟他說

425
00:20:40,340 --> 00:20:42,340
你嫂嫂要已經回到她的人民

426
00:20:42,340 --> 00:20:43,340
和她的神明身邊

427
00:20:43,340 --> 00:20:45,340
跟她回去吧

428
00:20:45,340 --> 00:20:48,340
After some persuasion Orpah turned back

429
00:20:48,340 --> 00:20:51,340
but not Ruth

430
00:20:51,340 --> 00:20:53,340
Because Ruth had faith

431
00:20:53,340 --> 00:20:58,340
She had faith in the midst of her difficulty

432
00:20:58,340 --> 00:21:00,340
to be a risk taker

433
00:21:00,340 --> 00:21:02,340
娥米勸了她的媳婦

434
00:21:02,340 --> 00:21:05,340
然後娥爾巴已經決定轉身回家鄉

435
00:21:05,340 --> 00:21:07,340
但是路德還是留下

436
00:21:07,340 --> 00:21:09,340
因為他想做一個冒險的

437
00:21:09,340 --> 00:21:12,340
Naomi said, your sister-in-law is going

438
00:21:12,340 --> 00:21:15,340
你嫂嫂已經離開了

439
00:21:15,340 --> 00:21:17,340
Go with her, go to your own people

440
00:21:17,340 --> 00:21:19,340
and go back to your own gods

441
00:21:19,340 --> 00:21:20,340
你跟著她走

442
00:21:20,340 --> 00:21:22,340
回去你自己的人民當中

443
00:21:22,340 --> 00:21:25,340
回去你們的神那裡吧

444
00:21:25,340 --> 00:21:29,340
And then the classic verse in chapter 16

445
00:21:29,340 --> 00:21:31,340
She confesses her love

446
00:21:31,340 --> 00:21:32,340
and her commitment

447
00:21:32,340 --> 00:21:34,340
and her faith to Naomi

448
00:21:34,340 --> 00:21:36,340
and to her God

449
00:21:36,340 --> 00:21:38,340
在經典的十六節之中

450
00:21:38,340 --> 00:21:41,340
路德是將他對於他婆婆的愛

451
00:21:41,340 --> 00:21:46,340
以及對於他婆婆的神那種忠心

452
00:21:46,340 --> 00:21:49,340
She says, don't urge me to leave you

453
00:21:49,340 --> 00:21:51,340
她說,不要勸我離開你

454
00:21:51,340 --> 00:21:52,340
Or to turn back from you

455
00:21:52,340 --> 00:21:54,340
Where you go, I will go

456
00:21:54,340 --> 00:21:56,340
And where you stay, I will stay

457
00:21:56,340 --> 00:21:59,340
Your people will be my people

458
00:21:59,340 --> 00:22:03,340
And your God will be my God

459
00:22:03,340 --> 00:22:05,340
路德說,不要勸我離開你

460
00:22:05,340 --> 00:22:07,340
轉去不跟隨你

461
00:22:07,340 --> 00:22:09,340
你往哪裏去,我又往哪裏去

